Description: Fragment of a plaster jar sealing bearing an indistinct stamped cartouche.
Curator's comments: On illegible stamps on plaster jar-sealings, Psamtek II or Apries, see W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 72 § 69.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 72 § 69) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.69, p.183, pl.25)
